---
import ArticleLayout from '../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
import Reassurance from '../components/Reassurance.astro';
import MidCta from '../components/MidCta.astro';
import PullQuote from '../components/PullQuote.astro';
import FaqSection from '../components/FaqSection.astro';
import CtaBlock from '../components/CtaBlock.astro';
import EnquiryForm from '../components/locked/EnquiryForm.astro';
import RelatedPanel from '../components/RelatedPanel.astro';

const slug = '/seafarer-mortgage-help';

const reassuranceLines = [
  'Paid in a foreign currency.',
  'Claiming the Seafarers Earnings Deduction.',
  'Rotational contracts with long spells at sea.',
  'Limited recent UK address history.',
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Do I need a specialist broker for a seafarer mortgage?',
    a: 'It helps a great deal. Seafarer income is read very differently from one lender to the next, and a broker who places these cases regularly knows which lenders treat your pay fairly. The work is in matching your circumstances to the right lender, not in the eligibility itself.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Will the Seafarers Earnings Deduction stop me getting a mortgage?',
    a: 'No. The deduction lowers your UK tax, not your earnings. A lender that understands seafarers works from your gross contractual pay rather than the low tax figure on your return, so the relief is not the obstacle. Lender choice is.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I get help if I am working abroad right now?',
    a: 'We can start a conversation, but you must be on UK soil to receive advice. We confirm your residency and circumstances properly before recommending anything, so the advice fits where you genuinely stand.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do I start?',
    a: 'Use the 60-second check and a Mortgage One adviser will review your answers and tell you where you stand. You can also call us on 01202 155992. You must be on UK soil to receive advice.',
  },
];

const relatedCards = [
  { title: 'Mortgages for seafarers', href: '/mortgage-as-a-seafarer', line: 'The full picture for seafarer mortgages.' },
  { title: 'Foreign currency income', href: '/seafarer-mortgage-foreign-currency-income', line: 'How lenders convert and discount non-sterling pay.' },
  { title: 'Seafarers Earnings Deduction mortgages', href: '/seafarers-earnings-deduction-mortgage', line: 'Getting a mortgage while you claim the Seafarers Earnings Deduction.' },
  { title: 'Merchant navy mortgages', href: '/merchant-navy-mortgage', line: 'Specialist help for merchant navy pay.' },
  { title: 'Check your eligibility', href: '/check', line: 'Five quick questions, about 60 seconds.' },
];
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Seafarer Mortgage Help: Specialist Advice | Mortgage One"
  description="Seafarer mortgage help from a specialist broker. The common hurdles, foreign currency, the Seafarers Earnings Deduction and residency, and how to clear them."
  eyebrow="Seafarer mortgage questions"
  heading="Seafarer mortgage help: getting the right advice"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { name: 'Seafarer mortgage help', href: slug },
  ]}
  scenario="seafarer"
>
  <p>
    Yes, seafarers get UK mortgages, and the help you need is usually less about eligibility and more about getting your
    income read correctly. The hurdles are well known: foreign currency pay, the Seafarers Earnings Deduction, long
    spells at sea and residency. None of them is a barrier with a lender that understands seafarers, and that is what
    specialist help gets you.
  </p>

  <Reassurance title="Situations we help with" lines={reassuranceLines} />

  <h2>What makes a seafarer mortgage different?</h2>
  <p>
    On paper a seafarer is a strong borrower with steady, contracted income. The trouble is that an automated high
    street check is built around PAYE payslips and a settled UK footprint, so foreign currency, a nil tax bill and time
    at sea can each trip it. Specialist help means taking your case to a lender that reads those features as normal,
    because for this line of work they are.
  </p>

  <h2>Foreign currency pay</h2>
  <p>
    If you are paid in US dollars or euros, a lender converts the income to sterling and applies a reduction to allow for
    the rate moving, then works from that figure. The size of the reduction varies, so the lender you choose matters more
    than the rate. We cover this in full on our
    <a href="/seafarer-mortgage-foreign-currency-income">foreign currency income</a> page.
  </p>

  <MidCta
    text="Not sure which hurdle is holding you up? Tell us how you are paid and we will tell you where you stand."
    scenario="seafarer"
    src={slug}
  />

  <h2>The Seafarers Earnings Deduction</h2>
  <p>
    The Seafarers Earnings Deduction (SED) is a relief from HM Revenue and Customs that removes UK income tax on
    qualifying earnings for work carried out outside the UK, claimed over an eligible period of at least 365 days
    according to HM Revenue and Customs. It is legitimate and well established, but it makes your taxable income look low,
    which an automated check can misread. The right lender works from your gross contractual pay instead. There is more
    on our <a href="/seafarers-earnings-deduction-mortgage">Seafarers Earnings Deduction</a> page.
  </p>

  <h2>Time at sea, rotation and merchant navy pay</h2>
  <p>
    Rotational contracts and long stretches away are routine, and a lender that knows the sector treats a settled
    rotation as stable employment rather than a gap. Merchant navy crews often combine all of these at once, which we
    cover on our <a href="/merchant-navy-mortgage">merchant navy mortgages</a> page.
  </p>

  <PullQuote quote="Seafarer mortgage help is rarely about whether you qualify. It is about taking your case to the lender that reads your income fairly." />

  <h2>How does Mortgage One help?</h2>
  <p>
    Mortgage One has access to plans from the whole of market and arranges seafarer cases as a core part of the business,
    not an exception to it. We give professional advice on which lender fits how you are paid, gather the evidence an
    underwriter needs, and put your case in front of the right desk. You must be on UK soil to receive advice, so we
    confirm your circumstances properly before recommending anything.
  </p>

  <MidCta
    text="Ready for an answer rather than another decline? Let an adviser place your case."
    label="Check Your Options"
    scenario="seafarer"
    src={slug}
  />

  <FaqSection items={faqs} />

  <CtaBlock
    heading="Get seafarer mortgage help"
    line="Tell us how you are paid and a Mortgage One adviser will review your answers."
    scenario="seafarer"
    src={slug}
  />

  <h2>Send us an enquiry</h2>
  <EnquiryForm scenario="seafarer" />

  <RelatedPanel cards={relatedCards} />

  <p class="risk-warning">
    Think carefully before securing your debts against your home. Your home may be repossessed if you do not keep up
    repayments on your mortgage.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>

<style>
  .risk-warning {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }
</style>
